*LPA 91W slowly moving northwestward but somewhat disorganized.  At 2PM today, the LPA was located about 160 km East of Davao City, Davao Del Sur (7.3N 126.9E). The chance of becoming a Tropical Cyclone (Bagyo) within the next 24 hours remains Low (<35% chance).

*LPA 91W,  a newly-formed disturbance over the South Philippine Sea.  At 8PM today, the LPA was located about 537 km East of Mati City, Davao Oriental (6.1N 131.0E). The chance of becoming a Tropical Cyclone (Bagyo) within the next 24 hours is Low (<35% chance).
This SLPA will not become a Tropical Cyclone (Bagyo) and based on the Current Typhoon Models - this disturbance is expected to dissipate in the coming days.
